ğŸ”¹ The Role of Sub-Dashboards

Sub-dashboards are dedicated, focused dashboards that provide detailed insights into specific AWS services or infrastructure components.

âœ… Key Benefits:
	1.	Deeper Analysis of Specific Components:
	â€¢	Each sub-dashboard focuses on one aspect, such as:
	â€¢	EC2 Performance
	â€¢	API Gateway Metrics
	â€¢	RDS Query Performance
	â€¢	VPC Network Traffic
	â€¢	Engineers can quickly zoom in on problem areas.
	2.	Improved Performance & Load Distribution:
	â€¢	Instead of overloading the main dashboard with complex queries, each sub-dashboard handles specific, detailed queries.
	â€¢	Ensures Grafana remains responsive.
	3.	Team-Based Access & Permissions:
	â€¢	Different teams (e.g., Ops, DevOps, SREs) may have their own customized sub-dashboards.
	â€¢	Permissions can be set so users only access relevant dashboards.
	4.	Better Troubleshooting Workflow:
	â€¢	When an issue is detected on the Single Pane View, engineers can click on a section to open the relevant sub-dashboard and investigate further.
	â€¢	Example Flow:
	â€¢	Main Dashboard Alert: â€œHigh API Gateway Latency ğŸš¨â€
	â€¢	Click on API Gateway â†’ Opens API GW Sub-Dashboard
	â€¢	View detailed breakdown: latency per endpoint, error rates, throttling metrics.

